   BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. -- American Medical International
Inc., a hospital company, said its acquisition has been
completed by IMA Holdings Corp., an investor group including
CS First Boston Group Inc.'s First Boston Corp. and the
Pritzker family of Chicago.
   The group acquired 86% of American Medical's 71.5 million
common shares outstanding in a tender offer late last year.
The company said American Medical shares will no longer trade
on the New York Stock Exchange.
