</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
DRUG MANUFACTURERS (DRG)
</IN>
<LP>
   MIDLAND, Mich. -- Dow Chemical Co. said it will purchase
from time to time in open-market or private transactions an
additional four million shares of Marion Merrell Dow Inc.,
raising its stake in the pharmaceutical concern to 68% from
the current 67%, or 186.3 million of the 278.3 million shares
outstanding.
   "Marion Merrell Dow is an outstanding value, and offers an
excellent investment opportunity for Dow," said Enrique C.
Falla, Dow Chemical's financial vice president and chief
financial officer. In New York Stock Exchange composite
trading yesterday, Marion Merrell shares closed at $25.375,
up 75 cents.
