BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)
</IN>
<LP>
   CINCINNATI -- The judge overseeing the bankruptcy-court
proceedings of Federated Department Stores Inc. and Allied
Stores Corp. approved an employee retention plan designed to
keep key managers from defecting from the retail companies.
   The plan will affect about 2,300 of Federated and Allied's
approximately 101,000 employees. They will be offered
employment contracts, termination agreements, enhanced
severance pay and bonuses. Federated and Allied, which are
units of Campeau Corp., filed for protection under Chapter 11
of the U.S. Bankruptcy Code Jan. 15.
</LP>
<TEXT>
