Vincent Aug Jr. will cost the companies about $10.6 million
in the first year and $11 million in the second year,
according to documents filed in federal bankruptcy court
here. In addition, $5 million a year will be available for
discretionary bonuses. Heads of stores, merchandise managers
and corporate vice presidents will be covered by the plan.
