<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Initial claims for regular state
unemployment benefits fell to a seasonally adjusted 338,000
during the week ended March 31 from 342,000 the previous
week, the Labor Department said.
   The number of people receiving regular state benefits in
the week ended March 24 was a seasonally adjusted 2,313,000,
