the Israelis during the 1990 third quarter. Several other
nations in the Middle East, Europe and the Far East have
expressed interest in buying Apaches for their own defense,
McDonnell Douglas said. A spokesman said that prior to the
Israeli purchase, the U.S. Army has ordered 807 of the
helicopters since their production began in 1983.
