<HL>
   International Brief -- Fokker N.V.:
   Aerospace Firm Reports Net
   For '89 More Than Tripled
</HL>
<DATE>
04/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8
</SO>
<CO>
   N.FOK
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Dutch aerospace group Fokker N.V., citing decreased
financing charges in 1989, reported that 1989 net profit more
than tripled. It said net rose to 42.4 million guilders
($22.5 million) from 13.3 million guilders in 1988.
   The aircraft builder said, "Fokker looks to the future
with confidence, not least in view of the present order book
of 10 billion guilders."
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said that its net profit picture for 1989 was
considerably improved by a reduction in financing charges to
55 million guilders from 64 million guilders in the year
earlier. In addition, Fokker's participating interests in
other companies contributed revenue of 15.9 million guilders
in 1989 compared with 8.6 million guilders in 1988.
</TEXT>
